cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper proposes a novel architecture for object classification that is extensively evaluated on six different datasets, mainly on three different medical sets, in addition to the natural MNIST, SVHN and CIFAR10. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The proposed architecture incorporates the Self-Attention mechanism as an integral layer within the Capsule Network (CapsNet) to significantly improve the results. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a new architecture for object classification that uses a Self-Attention mechanism to suppress irrelevant regions based on features analysis and highlights salient features useful for a specific task. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The proposed architecture uses a Capsule Network (CapsNet) that analyzes the relevant features and their spatial correlations inside the selected regions only. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper evaluates the proposed architecture on six different datasets, including medical sets, and shows that it outperforms the baseline CapsNet, ResNet-18 and DenseNet-40 not only in classification accuracy but also in robustness.
